cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about salient object detection using deep convolutional neural networks. The most relevant arXiv CS sub-category is Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) as the paper focuses on image analysis and feature extraction. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel network architecture that integrates low-level appearance features, high-level semantic features, and global context features, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of attention mechanisms and refinement modules, which are common techniques in deep learning and neural networks (cs.LG, cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed approach on benchmark datasets, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
